---
Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 4
  Paragraph: 15
Title: In The World Of Men
---
\"By doing my work through the examples of antiquity, I can be the
companion of ancient times. Though my words may in fact be lessons and
reproaches, they belong to ancient times and not to me. In this way,
though I may be blunt, I cannot he blamed. This is what I mean by being
a companion of antiquity. If I go about it in this way, will it do?"
